					<head>Commentary</head>
					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85013597" rend="visible">
						<summary>The book of Joshua with a Judeo-Arabic commentary of Japheth ben Ali ha-Levi.</summary>
						<textLang mainLang="he" otherLangs="jrb">Hebrew, Judeo-Arabic</textLang>
						<msItem rend="visible" class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85013597">
							<locus from="1r" to="217v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Perush </title>
							<title xml:lang="he">פרוש </title>
							<note>
								<p>Contains the pointed and accentuated Hebrew text, accompanied by an Arabic translation and commentary.</p>
								<p>The missing portion at the beginning comprises chapter 1:1-13.</p>
								<p>Has a number of masoretic notes.</p>
							</note>
							<author key="http://viaf.org/viaf/54984961">
								<persName key="http://viaf.org/viaf/54984961" xml:lang="en">Japheth ben Ali, ha-Levi,‏ active 10th century </persName>
								<persName key="http://viaf.org/viaf/54984961" xml:lang="he">יפת בן עלי, הלוי</persName>
							</author>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Paper codex of the 15th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="chart">
								<support>Paper codex</support>
								<extent>217 folios<dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
										<height>183</height>
										<width>140</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>135</height>
										<width>90</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>217 folios (+ 2 paper flyleaves at the beginning and 3 at the end).</p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>Originally 23 quires of 10 leaves each, except the last which has 6 leaves only.</p>
									<p>Quires signed with Hebrew letters on the right-hand upper corner of the first page, and marked with catchwords on the preceding page (the catchwords from page to page have been added later).</p>
									<p>Imperfect at the beginning (the first quire has been lost).</p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>The first quire has not been preserved.</p>
									<p>A number of folios have been more or less mutilated.</p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="1" ruledLines="13" writtenLines="13">
									<p>The pointed and accentuated Hebrew biblical text is embodied.</p>
									<p>Visible ruling with a hard-point.</p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="1">
							<summary>Square and semi-cursive script of 15th century.</summary>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="sole"/>
						</handDesc>
						<additions>
							<p>Folio 142 has been added later into the 15th quire.</p>
						</additions>
						<bindingDesc>
							<binding>
								<p>BM/BL in-house.</p>
								<p>Spine: 'Caraite Commentary on Joshua. Arabic. Brit. Mus. Oriental 2404.'</p>
							</binding>
						</bindingDesc>
